## Memory update protocol

1. After a session, write *learnings*, not transcript
2. One fact per entry, with a date
3. If a new entry contradicts an existing one, *update* the existing one — don't append
4. Move stale entries to "Outdated" before deleting (so they're recoverable in `git log`)
5. Run [agent-memory-curator skill](../skills/examples/agent-memory-curator) periodically

## What does NOT belong here
- Secrets, tokens, credentials
- PII without a retention policy
- Full chat transcripts (those go to `logs/`)
- Anything derivable from `git log` or current code
